The paper deals with capacity maximization in wireless networks, which is a problem in the intersection of information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The use of learning algorithms to solve the problem suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the consideration of dynamic link arrivals and departures suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY).
